<ab><lb n="1"/> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">δῆμος</w> <w lemma="θάπτω">ἔθαψε<unclear reason="damage">ν</unclear></w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἄτταλος"><supplied reason="lost">Ἄτ</supplied><lb n="2" break="no"/>ταλον</name> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλου</name> <supplied reason="lost">τοῦ</supplied>  <lb n="3"/> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἄτταλος">Ἀττάλου</name> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἑρμόλαος">Ἑρμολά<lb n="4" break="no"/>ου</name></persName></persName></persName></persName> <w lemma="παῖς">παῖδα</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὴν</w> <w lemma="ἡλικία">ἡλικίαν</w> <lb n="5"/> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="στεφανόω">ἐστεφάνωσεν</w> <w lemma="χρυσός">χρυ<lb n="6" break="no"/>σῷ</w> <w lemma="στέφανος">στεφάνωι</w> <space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  <lb n="6a"/>  <space extent="3" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>  </ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>The People buried Attalos son of Attalos son of Attalos son of Hermolaos, a boy in age-group, and crowned him with a gold crown.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The honorand was from a family of the civic aristocracy. The text also attests a formal organisation of children, and the civic practice of honours  for the children of the prominent</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography" n="none">
            <p>Unpublished.</p>
         </div>
